=begin pod

=head1 1. Install and Setup

=head2 Prerequisites

=item Raku (2026.04 or later)
=item C<zef> package manager
=item An OpenAI or Anthropic API key

=head2 Install the module

=begin code :lang<shell>
zef install Slangify::Tutorial
=end code

Or, to work from source:

=begin code :lang<shell>
git clone https://github.com/librasteve/Slangify-Tutorial
cd Slangify-Tutorial
zef install --/test .
=end code

=head2 Set your API key

C<LLM::Functions> picks up your key from the environment:

=begin code :lang<shell>
export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
=end code

=head2 Verify the install

=begin code :lang<raku>
use Slangify::Tutorial;

say parse-booking("Jane booked a table for 4 at 7:30pm tomorrow at Bistro Verde");
=end code

You should see a JSON string with C<name>, C<party>, C<time>, C<restaurant>,
and C<date> fields.

=end pod
